				What is Kihon?
			</h1>
			<p>
				The literal meaning of Kihon is the basics or fundamental. A karateka performs Kihon by practising 
				basics such as stances, punches, kicks and blocks; improving the strength and effectiveness 
				of their movements.
			</p><br>
			
			<img id="kihonImage" src = "images/kihon/kihon.jpg">

			<p>
				Similarly, practising basic moves can be seen in every other sport like football where the 
				footballers keep practising to improve and be better than other players. This principle applies to 
				Karate and it allows karateka to improve their overall karate skills and move up to the next rank.       

			</p>
